getValue

public java.lang.Integer getValue()
A Cells value may either be a clue or a big number. Note it is the calling classes responsibilty to check this Cell contains a value or erroneous data will be returned.

Returns:
The value (clue or big number) this Cells contains (assumes isSet()).

getRow

public java.lang.Integer getRow()
A cell always exists as part of a puzzle on a defined row, it is written as a static variable when the Cell object is created.

Although this variable is not used when accessing the Cell object (which is done via the Puzzle class which contains the Units is lies in), it is useful to cache it at creation time to reduce overhead later on.

Returns:
The row in which this cell lies
